<p>When page refresh that post request, form resubmission happened. I tried redirect after post request. but, it's not working when request have context. this context have form.errors because login.html show form error. How to resolve this issue? (without Message Framework)</p>  <pre><code>def do_login(request):   if request.method == 'POST':     form = LoginForm(request.POST)     if form.is_valid():       email = form.cleaned_data['email']       password = form.cleaned_data['password']       user = authenticate(email=email, password=password)       if user is not None:         login(request, user)         return redirect(reverse('root'))     else:       pass       # redirect cannot pass context, right?   else:     form = LoginForm() context = {     'form': form } return render(request, 'accounts/login.html', context=context) </code></pre>